    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SHIFT TOWER</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301401">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301401" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301401" filename="../figg13/G1301401.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Shift Tower Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the six retaining bolts and lockwashers. Separate the shift tower from the
                    shifter housing and gasket and lift straight up.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the shift lever housing on edge in the vise.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull up the boot. Depress the collar against the spring and remove the pin.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the spring retainer up the shift lever and remove the rock shaft snap ring.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tap the rock shaft free of the lever housing and remove the shift lever. Remove the seal
                    and discard.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift lever handle and slide the boot, spring retainer, spring, and lever
                    cover off the lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
